    "# Data Preparation Notebook\n",
    "## Depression Prediction using BRFSS 2023 Survey Data\n",
    "### Module: AI Futures (M7015) | Assessment 1\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook prepares the training dataset for a supervised machine learning model\n",
    "that predicts whether a survey respondent has been diagnosed with depression.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Data source:** The 2023 Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System (BRFSS), published\n",
    "annually by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). The BRFSS is the\n",
    "largest ongoing telephone health survey in the world, collecting data from over 400,000\n",
    "US adults each year on health behaviours, chronic conditions, and use of preventative\n",
    "services.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Target variable:** `ADDEPEV3` -- whether a respondent has ever been told by a doctor\n",
    "that they have a depressive disorder (binary: Yes / No).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Notebook structure:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Section | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| 1 | Imports and configuration |\n",
    "| 2 | Data acquisition |\n",
    "| 3 | Memory-efficient chunked loading |\n",
    "| 4 | Initial quality check |\n",
    "| 5 | Removing invalid responses |\n",
    "| 6 | Variable recoding and type correction |\n",
    "| 7 | Categorical encoding |\n",
    "| 8 | Outlier inspection |\n",
    "| 9 | Exploratory visualisation |\n",
    "| 10 | Class imbalance assessment |\n",
    "| 11 | Save final model-ready dataset |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note on a missing variable:** `SLEPTIM1` (average hours of sleep per night) was\n",
    "included in the original feature selection plan but is absent from the 2023 combined\n",
    "BRFSS file. Sleep deprivation is a clinically validated predictor of depression, so\n",
    "its absence is noted here as a limitation of this dataset."
   ]
