    "---\n",
    "## Section 2: Data Acquisition\n",
    "\n",
    "The BRFSS 2023 dataset is downloaded directly from the CDC's official server. The raw\n",
    "file is a SAS Transport (XPT) format file distributed inside a ZIP archive.\n",
    "\n",
    "Two practical issues are handled here:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Issue 1 -- 403 Forbidden error:** The CDC server blocks requests from Python's default\n",
    "user agent string. A browser-style user agent header is passed to the request so the\n",
    "server treats it as a standard web browser download.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Issue 2 -- Trailing space in filename:** The CDC's ZIP archive contains the file named\n",
    "`'LLCP2023.XPT '` (with a trailing space). This causes a `FileNotFoundError` if the\n",
    "filename is hardcoded. The filename is read directly from the ZIP manifest and stripped\n",
    "of whitespace before use."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "33755c4b-62c7-491e-b670-626136c2c9a5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Downloading BRFSS 2023 dataset (~64 MB ZIP) from CDC...\n",
      "Download complete.\n",
      "ZIP contains: ['LLCP2023.XPT ']\n",
      "Renamed 'LLCP2023.XPT ' to 'LLCP2023.XPT' (removed trailing space)\n",
      "Dataset file ready: 'LLCP2023.XPT'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Downloading BRFSS 2023 dataset (~64 MB ZIP) from CDC...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Browser-style user agent prevents the CDC server returning a 403 Forbidden error\n",
    "headers = {\n",
    "    \"User-Agent\": (\n",
    "        \"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) \"\n",
    "        \"AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) \"\n",
    "        \"Chrome/122.0.0.0 Safari/537.36\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "response = requests.get(ZIP_URL, headers=headers)\n",
    "response.raise_for_status()\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(LOCAL_ZIP, \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "    f.write(response.content)\n",
    "print(\"Download complete.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract the ZIP and handle the CDC's trailing-space filename quirk\n",
    "with zipfile.ZipFile(LOCAL_ZIP, \"r\") as zip_ref:\n",
    "    file_list = zip_ref.namelist()\n",
    "    print(f\"ZIP contains: {file_list}\")\n",
    "    zip_ref.extractall()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Locate the XPT file by searching the manifest rather than hardcoding the name\n",
    "xpt_entry = next(\n",
    "    (f for f in file_list if f.strip().upper().endswith(\".XPT\")), None\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "if xpt_entry is None:\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"No XPT file found in ZIP. Contents: {file_list}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strip the trailing space and rename the file on disk\n",
    "clean_name = xpt_entry.strip()\n",
    "if xpt_entry != clean_name:\n",
    "    os.rename(xpt_entry, clean_name)\n",
    "    print(f\"Renamed '{xpt_entry}' to '{clean_name}' (removed trailing space)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "LOCAL_XPT = clean_name\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset file ready: '{LOCAL_XPT}'\")"
   ]
