    "---\n",
    "## Section 4: Initial Quality Check\n",
    "\n",
    "Before any cleaning, the raw dataset is inspected for missing values and data types.\n",
    "This establishes a baseline and confirms which variables require attention.\n",
    "\n",
    "The BRFSS dataset does not use `NaN` for missing values. Instead, missing and invalid\n",
    "responses are encoded as **sentinel codes**:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Code | Meaning |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `7` or `77` | Don't know / Not sure |\n",
    "| `9` or `99` | Refused to answer |\n",
    "\n",
    "These must be identified and removed before modelling. For example, `INCOME3 = 99`\n",
    "does not mean \"very high income\" -- it means the respondent refused to answer.\n",
    "Treating it as a numeric value would corrupt the model entirely."
   ]
