    "---\n",
    "## Section 5: Removing Invalid Responses (Sentinel Codes)\n",
    "\n",
    "Each variable is cleaned individually, with the valid code range documented alongside\n",
    "the removal step. Rows containing sentinel codes are **removed entirely** rather than\n",
    "imputed.\n",
    "\n",
    "Imputing a refused response (e.g. replacing \"Refused to state income\" with a median\n",
    "value) would introduce false data and misrepresent the respondent's actual situation.\n",
    "Removal is the appropriate clinical data practice here.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Data leakage prevention:** `_MENT14D` (days of poor mental health in the past month)\n",
    "was considered as a feature but deliberately excluded. It directly measures a core\n",
    "symptom of depression, meaning the model would predict depression from its own\n",
