    "## Section 10: Class Imbalance Assessment\n",
    "\n",
    "The target variable (`ADDEPEV3`) is **imbalanced**: approximately 21% of respondents\n",
    "report a depression diagnosis. This creates a significant modelling challenge.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why imbalance is a problem:**\n",
    "A naive model that predicts \"No depression\" for every single respondent would achieve\n",
    "approximately 79% accuracy without learning anything useful. Accuracy is therefore a\n",
    "misleading metric for this dataset and must not be used as the primary evaluation\n",
    "measure.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mitigation strategy:**\n",
    "- `class_weight='balanced'` will be applied to all classifiers in the modelling\n",
    "  notebook. This adjusts the penalty for misclassifying the minority class\n",
    "  (depression = 1), forcing the model to pay more attention to correctly identifying\n",
    "  genuine cases of depression.\n",
    "- Primary evaluation metrics will be **ROC-AUC** and **F1 Score**, both of which\n",
    "  account for class imbalance and are standard in clinical machine learning literature."
   ]
