    "## Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook has prepared a clean, model-ready dataset for predicting depression using\n",
    "the BRFSS 2023 survey data. The table below summarises every decision made during the\n",
    "preparation process.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Decision | Detail |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Download method** | Browser-style user agent used to bypass CDC server restrictions |\n",
    "| **Memory management** | Chunked reading (10,000 rows at a time) to avoid kernel crashes |\n",
    "| **Sentinel code removal** | BRFSS codes 7, 9, 77, and 99 removed entirely rather than imputed |\n",
    "| **Data leakage prevention** | `_MENT14D` excluded as it directly measures a depression symptom |\n",
    "| **BMI encoding** | Divided by 100 to restore true BMI values from BRFSS storage format |\n",
    "| **Smoking recoding** | Recoded to an ordinal severity scale (0=Never to 3=Daily) |\n",
    "| **Diabetes simplification** | Gestational and pre-diabetes collapsed into a single binary flag |\n",
    "| **Type correction** | Whole-number codes converted from float64 to int64 |\n",
    "| **MARITAL encoding** | One-hot encoded with Married as the reference category |\n",
    "| **BMI outliers** | Retained -- rare but physiologically plausible at the 0.20% rate observed |\n",
    "| **Class imbalance** | Documented as approx 5:1; all models will use `class_weight='balanced'` |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key limitation:** `SLEPTIM1` (average hours of sleep per night) was planned as a\n",
    "feature but is absent from the 2023 combined BRFSS file. Sleep deprivation is a\n",
    "clinically established predictor of depression; its exclusion limits the model's\n",
    "ability to capture this pathway and should be noted in the final write-up.\n",
